Sentencas: La1-xSrxCo1-yFeyO3-delta (LSCF) and La1-xSrxMnO3-delta (LSM) are typical cathode materials for solid oxide fuel cells (SOFC).
Titulo: Insight into the Electrospinning Process for SOFC Cathode Nanofibers

Sentencas: The nanofibers of these materials prepared by electro-spinning technology show excellent electrochemical performance.
Titulo: Insight into the Electrospinning Process for SOFC Cathode Nanofibers

Sentencas: In this work, the electrospinning process for these two materials was investigated in detail.
Titulo: Insight into the Electrospinning Process for SOFC Cathode Nanofibers

Sentencas: The viscosity and the conductivity of the electrospinning solution were tested.
Titulo: Insight into the Electrospinning Process for SOFC Cathode Nanofibers

Sentencas: The focus was on evaluating the effect of nitrate concentration on the minimum voltage for a nondripping drop (V-min).
Titulo: Insight into the Electrospinning Process for SOFC Cathode Nanofibers

Sentencas: A model of the electrospinning process was proposed to understand the electrospinning process intuitively.
Titulo: Insight into the Electrospinning Process for SOFC Cathode Nanofibers

Sentencas: The results show that adding LSCF and LSM nitrate to the electrospinning solution affects the solution viscosity by increasing it 3-fold compared to the nitrate-free solution, followed by increases in conductivity and V-min.
Titulo: Insight into the Electrospinning Process for SOFC Cathode Nanofibers

Sentencas: This results in a difference in the size and morphology of the nanofibers, probably depending on the types of element, the valence state, and the content of metal ions per unit volume.
Titulo: Insight into the Electrospinning Process for SOFC Cathode Nanofibers

Sentencas: It is found that 470.6-2267 mP center dot s and 7.69-17.07 mS/cm are the appropriate values for the viscosity and conductivity, respectively, to obtain relative uniform nanofibers by applying a V-min in the range of 17-26 kV. The results in this work are expected to serve as a reference for the industrialization of LSM/LSCF nanofiber electrodes and the preparation of other SOFC nanofiber cathodes by electrospinning.
Titulo: Insight into the Electrospinning Process for SOFC Cathode Nanofibers
